text:
i 10000% get that lots of people are annoyed about ü¶û. there's a ton of hype and a ton of grifters trying to make a quick buck (hello mute and block feature).

but there's also genuinely a lot of really interesting things happening in the space. 

even if on the surface it seems like a waste of time, the experimenting happening right now will definitely have a big impact on the future of AI usage. and i think THAT is what's really exciting right now. seeing trends emerge.

following along with that isn't for everyone. it's a firehose.

but i *do* think if you have any interest in AI, it's worth at least checking in every week to see what folks are doing in the space.

text:
The real value I got out of Openclaw was more in strategy than the actual output

Yesterday it prepared me a detailed 15 page PDF on how I could get SEO to the next level

In fact, I was very dismissive when setting it up, but got totally surprised when "John Wick" (my clawdebot) came up with this

I just dumped everything about my business, gave it sandboxed read access to Posthog & Chartmogul

It went ahead & analyzed which pages could get more ranking

The best way I'd recommend to use it is to prompt
- full context of your business
- tell what's been working for you so far
- what your revenue goals are & why
- ask it to surprise you

It works really well once you do it
